It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house, where nothing has been done except for a bit of decorating.
The disgusting electric fireplace and the fireplace floor have to go. We have to surround the chimney, replace and smooth out the fallen plaster. Then build a custom-made wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch.
The dirty part of the job is done.
We found a few dead birds behind the chimney, very dried out :(.
Everything ready for the plasterer next week.
The small side niche has turned out well.
Here comes a new wardrobe in (but we haven't even started on the design yet)
Oh, look what we've found behind the heater!
And we've even thought of installing this nice little ventilation flap, so the chimney doesn't get wet.
The chimney sweep has installed the cowl and cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the crows that like to nest up there.
The tiler is finished. Tomorrow the floor will be laid.
The cork mat is lying, I have cobbled together a sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner from a roll of toilet paper 😂
The tiles for the floor are finished and can be laid. We're taking a tea break right now.
"Ugh. It's going slow today due to super complicated cuts around the doorposts so we have a smooth transition into the hallway (where the floor is also being re-laid). @user45 has cursed me out."
Finished, but it was at the end! The crown was the dreadful assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The flooring in the hall and all baseboards are still missing. The decorator is coming in a month so we're currently in a rough-stage look.
Some DIY work in the evening to saw or chisel out the lower sections around the door posts, so that the floor will fit snugly underneath.
The cork mat is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway. Then at 5 o'clock in the morning, we left to pick up item 1 in Heathrow, then a nap, and sprint to the end in the hallway, the skirting boards are on. The joints will be made when the adhesive is dry.
